To prove the equality, we first observe that both sides are constructed from the same list (`fin_range n`), but with different mapping functions. The key step is to use the fact that mapping `List.map` twice is equivalent to composing the functions (i.e., `(l.map f).map g = l.map (g ∘ f)`). We then rewrite the expressions using this property and confirm that the transformed values are the same.

